task.summary:
Made some modifications to work around the weird prefixes Laravel Echo adds to broadcast messages when delivered/instantiated by Redis. These changes mean that the beta and the live site will be handling messages from and sending to the same queue and channel. It appears that the only possibility of making the channel specific to the site is on application level - that is, adding something to

```
    public function broadcastOn()
    {
        return new Channel('messages');
    }
```

e.g. a "-site" suffix. For the time being none of this is very important as the messages are mostly 'refresh' ones which have no impact to the system whatsoever.

